  "algorithm_summary": "This phenotype algorithm identifies patients with low HDL levels by: 1) Starting with PMRP cohort members who consented and didn't withdraw; 2) Identifying baseline HDL results before any censoring events; 3) Determining censoring dates for conditions/medications that affect HDL (cancer, diabetes, thyroid disorders, statins, fibrates, niacin, estrogen); 4) Using the earliest HDL result before any censoring event as baseline; 5) Classifying low HDL as <40 mg/dl for males and <50 mg/dl for females; 6) Requiring subjects to be age 18+ at baseline HDL measurement. The algorithm includes complex logic for identifying diabetes and thyroid conditions using multiple diagnosis codes across different time periods, lab values, and medication mentions in clinical notes.",
